description: "Xantan County is about the people you remember on your way out of town. Its seven loosely connected short stories about mythologized local heroes, superstitions and those quiet moments alone when you’re forced to face the noisiest parts of your life. They’re character driven stories about identity and growing up, moving on, life and—Love, in whatever way that presents itself. Between friends, family, partners. It’s the story of a small town on the fringe of a big city and how even the most seemingly unremarkable moments become part of the fabric there in."--Publisher's description at Lulu books
name: Xantan County
